**TO-DO LIST APPLICATION \- README**

A simple command-line To-do list application built with Java that allows users to manage their tasks efficiently. The application supports task creation, updating tasks, categorization and persistent storage using JSON files.

1. **FEATURES**

1. **Task Management:** You can add, remove, update and view tasks.  
2. **Task Organization:** You can add tasks under category and filter it using the category.  
3. **Priority Setting:** Assign priorities to the tasks. Options available are HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW.  
4. **Due date support:** Add due dates to the tasks.  
5. **Overdue detection:** Indicates tasks which are not completed past due date.  
6. **Status Tracking:** Mark tasks as complete/incomplete.  
7. **Search functionality:** Search tasks by title.  
8. **Bulk Operations:** Clear completed tasks or all tasks.  
9. **File Persistence:** Tasks automatically saved to JSON file.  
10. **Rich CLI interface:** Formatted tables with emoji indicators  
11. **Task Statistics:** View completion stats at startup

 **III. REQUIREMENTS**

1. Java 8 or higher  
2. Gson library for JSON serialization  
3. Maven (recommended for dependency management)

| Dependencies \<dependency\>     \<groupId\>com.google.code.gson\</groupId\>     \<artifactId\>gson\</artifactId\>     \<version\>2.8.9\</version\> \</dependency\> |
| :---- |

**IV. INSTALLATION AND SETUP**

**Option 1: Clone and Run**

1. **Clone the repository**

| git clone https://github.com/ritikaa24k/todo-list-app.git cd todo-list-app |
| :---- |

2. **Download dependencies \- Using Terminal (Recommended)**

In VS Code terminal, navigate to the lib directory and download JARs:

| cd lib *\# Download Gson* curl \-O https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/google/code/gson/gson/2.10.1/gson-2.10.1.jar *\# Download JUnit and Hamcrest* curl \-O https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/junit/junit/4.13.2/junit-4.13.2.jar curl \-O https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/hamcrest/hamcrest-core/1.3/hamcrest-core-1.3.jar cd ..  |
| :---- |

3. **If compiling manually (ensure Gson is in classpath)**

| javac \-cp "lib/gson-2.8.9.jar" src/com/todoapp/\*.java src/com/todoapp/\*/\*.java java \-cp "src:lib/gson-2.8.9.jar" com.todoapp.TodoApp |
| :---- |

**Option 2: IDE setup**

1. Import project into your IDE (IntelliJ IDEA, Eclipse, VS Code)  
2. Add Gson library to project dependencies.  
3. Run TodoApp.java main method

**Download Gson JAR**

| \# Create lib directory mkdir lib \# Download Gson (or use Maven to manage dependencies) \# Place gson-2.8.9.jar in lib/ directory  |
| :---- |

**VI. TESTING THE APPLICATION**  
**Manual Testing Checklist**  
**Basic functionality:**

1. Create tasks with title only  
2. Create tasks with full details   
3. View all tasks in formatted table  
4. Mark tasks as complete/incomplete  
5. Update existing tasks  
6. Delete individual tasks  
   

**Advanced Features:**

1. Search tasks by title (also includes partial matches)  
2. Filter tasks by category.  
3. Clear completed tasks only  
4. Clear all tasks  
5. Verify data persistence

**Edge cases:**

1. Empty task title (throws an error)  
2. Invalid date format (prompts retry, past dates)  
3. Non \- existent task ID operations

**Test Data Scenarios**  
**Sample test session:**  
Run these commands in sequence to test:  
1\. Add task: "Learn Java" (description: "Complete online course")  
2\. Add detailed task: (HIGH priority, tomorrow's date, "Career" category)    
3\. View all tasks  
4\. Mark first task complete  
5\. Search for "Java"  
6\. View tasks by category "Career"  
7\. Update second task description  
8\. Clear completed tasks  
9\. Exit and restart \- verify tasks persist

**VII. DESIGN APPROACH**

**Key design decisions**

1. File-based Storage: JSON format for human-readable data persistence.  
2. Auto-save: Tasks automatically saved after each operation  
3. Rich CLI: Formatted tables and emoji indicators for better UX  
4. Input validation: Comprehensive error handling and user prompts  
5. Extensible: Easy to add new features or change storage mechanism

**Architecture**

**MVC Pattern:**  
Separation of model(Task), View(CLI), and controller(TaskService)  
**Repository pattern:**  
File repository abstracts data persistence  
**Service layer:**  
TaskService handles business logic and validation

**Data Flow**

| User Input → TodoApp (CLI) → TaskService → FileRepository → JSON File                 ↓             Task Model ← TaskService ← FileRepository ← JSON File  |
| :---- |
